Law firm DWF has made two executive partner appointments in its Scottish practice.
Paul Pignatelli and Wayne Lawrence have been appointed as executive partners to the firm's Edinburgh and Glasgow offices respectively.
Pignatelli and Lawrence, who each have more than 15 years’ experience as corporate partners, will now be responsible for “driving forward DWF’s strategic business objectives”.
DWF managing partner and chief executive, Andrew Leaitherland, said: “We have ambitious plans for DWF in Scotland, and Paul and Wayne have the leadership experience and collaborative approach to help deliver our strategic business goals.
“The executive partner role is pivotal in shaping a strategy for each office to ensure we continue to effectively support our clients and people.
“It is with the full support of their colleagues that we wish Paul and Wayne all the best in their new roles.”
